Description.LocalizedString: Baermar noticed the crowd start to dwindle. To win back the audience, he hopped onto the edge of the nearby fountain and did a little dance as he played.
Once the show was over, they walked through the crowd with their hats out, thanking the audience for their generosity.
Aestri sang a song about a gelatinous cube that ate naughty children. The kids in the audience listened with eyes like saucers.

An icy wind rocked the bridge as they moved. They were ill-prepared for the bitter cold.
Baermar's heart raced as he lunged for his friend. Grabbing her hand in the nick of time, he mustered all his strength to keep her from falling.
Once they reached the other side, their legs gave out and they collapsed. After a moment of stunned silence, they both let out a nervous laugh.
Aestri tested each plank of the bridge before taking her next step. Even so, a rotted plank split in two beneath her foot, and she dropped through the hole.

She couldn't believe it. The silver seashell was buried just off the shore, under a rock shaped like a pyramid. She pulled the feather from her cap, eager to record her journey.
She held the silver seashell to her ear. Inside, a voice as wild and vast as the ocean sang about a kingdom beneath the waves.
She transcribed the song and drew the island on her map. Her prize sought, she buried the silver seashell once again, for another adventurer to find someday.
The bandits appeared from behind the trees, crossbows out. He held his lute and strummed a soothing tune.
As the bandits prepared to fire, something changed. They listened to the melodic lute and one after another, they fell asleep.
Baermar and Aestri made it to the other side of the forest, to the harbor town where they could charter a boat.
